definition: to obey/to follow/to arrange/to make reasonable/along/favorable

sentences.english: You work on your muscle groups in a certain order.
sentences.chinese: 對各個肌肉羣，你是在按照一個特定的順序進行。

sentences.english: These elements can be sorted, or processed in the order they appear.
sentences.chinese: 可以對這些元素排序，或以其出現的順序處理它們。

sentences.english: The ampersand (&) characters between the sibling element subpatterns indicate that any order is acceptable.
sentences.chinese: 兄弟元素子範式之間的豎線表示允許任何順序。

sentences.english: The Organic development sequence of Alisma orientale in early stage of ontogeny was studied.
sentences.chinese: 研究了澤瀉個體發育早期的器官發育順序。

sentences.english: Thus parts sequences of subassemblies can be automatically planned.
sentences.chinese: 由此，完成子裝配體內零件的自動順序規劃。

sentences.english: The organization templates are presented in increasing order of formality.
sentences.chinese: 我們依照形式化遞增的順序介紹組織模板。

sentences.english: Set you number of shots, sequence and time.
sentences.chinese: 你還可以設定拍片的張數，順序和時間。

sentences.english: We compile the instruction list of AWCDPR by the method of sequence control.
sentences.chinese: 採用順序控制編程方法編寫搶答器的指令表程序。

sentences.english: Ultimately, of course, the birth-order debate will never be entirely settled.
sentences.chinese: 最後，當然對於出生順序的爭論將永遠不會完全平息。

sentences.english: Analysis of the retrograde sequence of AP activation may localize and ablate the APs successfully.
sentences.chinese: 仔細分析旁路逆傳激動順序可以精確定位，成功消蝕。

sentences.english: It's got three extra tracks and the order's slightly different.
sentences.chinese: 有三條額外的音軌而且順序方面有點不同。

sentences.english: There is an interesting folktale about how the order of the 12 animals was determined.
sentences.chinese: 民間有種關於12生肖順序的有趣傳說。

sentences.english: Please take yours to get your note-books.
sentences.chinese: 請按順序取走你們的筆記本。

sentences.english: Any gaps in the sequence will indicate the books that have not yet been returned.
sentences.chinese: 順序號中的任何間隔將表示尚未歸還的圖書。

sentences.english: Take order and serve the guest according to the sequence.
sentences.chinese: 根據順序，爲客人點單並服務。

definition: to differentiate/to draw a distinction/to divide into categories
to make a choice (between several alternatives)/a choice/an option/an alternative
